com.topjohnwu.superuser.io

Class SuFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.File
      • com.topjohnwu.superuser.io.SuFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<File>

    public class SuFile
extends File
    A File implementation using root shell.

    All methods for this class will be backed by executing commands via the global root shell. The Shell instance will be acquired via Shell.getShell().

    This class has the exact same behavior as a normal File, however non of the operations are atomic. This is a limitation of using shells, be aware of it.

    For full functionality, the environment require: rm, rmdir, readlink, mv, ls, mkdir, touch, and stat. These tools are available on modern Android versions with toybox, however for consistent results using busybox would be desirable. Some operations could have oddities without busybox due to the lack of tools or different behavior of the tools, check the method descriptions for more info before using them.

    There are also handy factory methods SuFile.open(...) for obtaining File instances. These factory methods will return a normal File instance if the underlying shell does not have root access, or else returns a SuFile instance.

      • setLastModified

        public boolean setLastModified(long time)
        Sets the last-modified time of the file or directory named by this abstract pathname.

        Note: On older Android devices, the touch commands accepts a different timestamp format than GNU touch. This shell implementation uses the format accepted in GNU coreutils, which is the same in toybox and busybox, so the operation might fail on older Android versions without busybox.

        Overrides:
        setLastModified in class File
        Parameters:
        time - The new last-modified time, measured in milliseconds since the epoch.
        Returns:
        true if and only if the operation succeeded; false otherwise.
